Comment: I really wish Iron Man had been released on January 2 in the year 2007.  And that 2007 would have obviously been the year that the Marvel cinematic universe began not 2008.  I strongly would have much rather preferred if Iron Man had been released on January 2 2007 and that 2007 would have been the year that the Marvel cinematic universe started.  But I guess that's just me in my personal opinion and point of view cause I hate the year the Marvel cinematic universe began.  The fact that it started in 2008 pisses me off so much.  But it's not like that's the only reason Marvel fucked up from the start.  It's not just because they didn't start the Marvel cinematic universe in 2007 like they should have beginning with Iron Man.  It's also the fact that Marvel made a huge mistake ever promising Terrence Howard a lot of money in the Iron Man sequel as well which if they were smart and had their head's on straight at the time they would have never said or done.  They would have paid Terrence Howard what they could for the sequel and had what the other actors and actresses got in for money in the sequel private.  Then the Marvel cinematic universe would have been off to a great start but sadly they fucked up which is why I only love the first two movies in the Marvel cinematic universe being Iron Man and The Incredible Hulk.

Protecting the blue glow in his chest. 


He hid all his feelings behind a mask
Covering the guilt on his chest, the red on his hands
As he completed each mission, each task
Following no man's commands. 

His heart was broken too often to be counted, 
Failed by those he loved and trusted, 
But no matter what, he geared up
In his suit of armour; red and gold crusted

He won't let the enemies near, 
He'll sacrifice himself to do what's right, 
Till his very last breath, he'll fight. 

'Genius, billionare, playboy, philanthropist' he might be,

Yet to forget and move on, he'll try as hard as he can

Title: Iron Man - Trailer [HD]
Comment: It's crazy to think that the entire MCU started off with a movie about a Billionaire Genius who invents a Iron Suit. I mean just the fact that this movie actually did good at all is so lucky. I mean imagine someone comes up to you back in early 2000s when the only good Superhero films are the 1980's Tim Burrton Batman Film, the X-Men Films (except for X-Men The Last Stand because people hate that) & Sam Raimi's first 2 Spider-Man films (because the 3rd one wasn't that good) & they are like "Dude. Did you hear about that new Iron Man movie coming out?" & you're like "What's it about?" & they say "It's about this billionaire genius who builds an Iron Suit that can fly & shoot lasers." I mean to be honest, if you've never read any of the comics, that sounds like something that would be good on paper, but be cheesy on screen. But it was actually successful. & the fact that the MCU turned into a Cinematic Universe that crosses over with all the films is incredible. If it wasn't for Iron Man, we wouldn't be excited for Avengers Endgame. We'd probably be excited for the newest Batman movie coming out or something Superhero.

Iron Man is seriously so much more than just my favorite superhero :,)
